limerick_list.text:
Drink your chocolate the Mexican way;
Get the powder or tablets—just pay.
The brand's Abuelita;
More sweet, señorita,
Than the chocolate you're drinking today.

The news from my doc was traumatic;
My lungs are now atelectatic
Cuz the sacs have collapsed;
Ventilation has lapsed.
My oxygen need is emphatic!

John's complacent and Marsha's a doer;
She's a risk-taker, he is unsure.
She leads the parade;
He's laid back but not laid,
So their love life is down in the sewer.

"Can you spare me a dime?"—yet again!
So I look through my pockets—in vain.
He has asked twice before;
I've no more left in store;
I am changeless, and so will remain.

Of all of the crimes that exist
There's a few that are worst on the list:
	Regicide, patricide;
	Genocide, matricide;
And being an accordionist.

Shooting trophies comes easy, indeed;
Lazy hunters get all that they need.
Countless killings await;
Daily bags will be great.
At the game ranch, it's all guaranteed.

My trapezoid went all askew;
I connected the dots, but misdrew.
In an "X" two lines crossed;
With the parallels lost,
Then an antiparallelogram grew.

Life at sea has pernicious effects:
Scabby knees from hard scrubbing of decks;
Skin the texture of leather
From sea spray and weather;
Plus it's donkey's years since I've had sex.

For my eight-year-old princess's sake,
We've one heck of a party to make.
We've balloons and a clown;
We have painted the town;
We—my God! We've forgotten the cake!

The Central's the longest of all;
It connects much of London's great sprawl.
Many stations are packed,
And you risk getting whacked;
Getting onto the train's like a brawl!

Poop and vomit have caused it to clog;
It smells worse than a cesspit-dunked dog.
Loopy's loo's cracked and reeking;
Brown matter's been leaking.
No wonder he calls it "the bog".

When you leave someone out of the loop;
Or tell tales, tattle, rat out and snoop;
Or are lacking the grace
To converse face-to-face,
You're a rotten "behind one's back" poop!

A bloke who will bore you to sleep;
A pest who may cause you to leap
From the roof of your house;
An introvert louse;
An eccentric—that's me, I'm a creep.

Three mice on the run, sight-impaired;
One wife of a farmer, not scared.
She strikes from behind,
Decaudation in mind;
Three quick blows, three blind-mouse bottoms bared.

To the music's conclusion we wend;
Every rhythm and chord sets a trend.
We go slow, reverential,
For phrases cadential;
The song is now over.  The End.

Add an affix to some random word;
Derivation is what has occurred —
As in danced comes from dance,
Or perchance came by chance;
But renege formed from "nege"? That's absurd.

A dragon is green and breathes fire;
It has wings pterodactyls admire;
And the thing it loves most
Is an afternoon's roast
Of stray hobbits about on the shire.

Half a shilling would buy you a tune;
The rye in your pocket—a boon.
In the pie were a score
Of young blackbirds (plus four);
A surprise would be served very soon.
